This paper is likely to belong to the sub-category of Computational Linguistics (cs.CL) as it deals with the extraction of potential entries for a category from an online corpus. It also involves the use of algorithms for generating semantic lexicons, which is a common topic in the field of computational linguistics. 

It could also belong to the sub-category of Information Retrieval (cs.IR) as the algorithm presented in the paper involves the extraction of relevant terms from a corpus, which is a common task in information retrieval. 

The sub-category of Machine Learning (cs.LG) is also a possibility as the algorithm presented in the paper involves the use of statistical techniques for identifying potential entries for a category. 

The sub-category of Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) is also a possibility as the paper deals with the automatic generation of semantic lexicons, which is a common task in natural language processing, a subfield of AI. 

Finally, the sub-category of Deep Learning (cs.DL) is also a possibility as the algorithm presented in the paper involves the use of neural networks for identifying potential entries for a category.
